  "onnx_opset": 15,
  "pipeline_version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Canonical Python<->Java feature contract for the Phase 2b pitch_outcome_post model. 41 features: pre-pitch Tier 1+2+3 (31) + post-pitch Tier 4 (10: pitch_type_int, release_speed_mph, plate_x_in, plate_z_in, pfx_x_in, pfx_z_in, spin_rate_rpm, spin_axis_deg, release_pos_x_in, release_pos_z_in). Per-class isotonic calibration applied post-ONNX (Java) using calibrator.json. Tier 4 columns pre-2024 are NULL (pybaseball pre-V008 schema didn't capture them) \u2014 LightGBM handles NaN natively. Sister contract to feature_pipeline.json (pitch_outcome_pre).",
  "notes": "The pre-commit hook protects feature_pipeline.json only; this sibling contract's schema_hash is verified at Java startup (FeaturePipelinePitchPost.load) and at registry registration (rule 7). Hand-edits must re-run the pre-commit hook's recompute snippet against this path.",
